For Debian based distros
$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt install build-essential zlib1g-dev \
libncurses5-dev libgdbm-dev libnss3-dev \
libssl-dev libreadline-dev libffi-dev curl

$ cd Python-3.*
./configure

If you're using apt or dnf for installing packages, use the package manager to remove Python and then install

$ sudo make install

If you'd like to install multiple instances of Python
$ sudo make altinstall

python3 --version
